CONSTRUCTOR is use to initialize the object.

Each time an object is created using "new()" keyword at least one constructor is invoked to assign initial values( Default Constructor).

TYPES OF CONSTRUCTOR:-
(a) No-argument constructor (no parameter)
    
    --> Default constructor provides the default values to the object like 0, null, etc. depending on the type.
    
    EXAMPLE:-
              class ConstructorClass 
               { 
                  	int num; 
                  	String name; 
                    ConstructorClass() 
                    { 
                	    	System.out.println("Constructor called"); 
                  	} 
               } 

              class MainClass 
              { 
                	public static void main (String[] args) 
                	{  
                    		ConstructorClass cons = new ConstructorClass(); 
                    		System.out.println(cons.name); 
	                     	System.out.println(cons.num); 
                	} 
              } 
              
      OUTPUT:-
                 Constructor called
                 null
                 0




(b) Parameterized Constructor (with parameter)

    --> If we want to initialize fields of the class with your own values, then use a parameterized constructor.
    
    EXAMPLE:-
                class ConstructorClass 
                {
                    String name; 
                    int id;   
                   
                   ConstructorClass(String name, int id) 
                   { 
                        this.name = name; 
                        this.id = id; 
                    } 
                 } 
  
                class MainClass 
                { 
                     public static void main (String[] args) 
                     { 
                          ConstructorClass cons = new ConstructorClass("sam", 1); 
                          System.out.println("Name :" + Cons.name + 
                                                     " and Id :" + cons.id); 
                      } 
                } 
                
    OUTPUT:-
              Name :sam and Id :1
              
              

** We don't write the return value statement but constructor return current class instance.**

**How constructors are different from methods in Java?

  (a) Constructor(s) must have the same name as the class within which it defined while it is not necessary for the method in java.
  (b) Constructor(s) do not return any type while method(s) have the return type or void if does not return any value.
  (c) Constructor is called only once at the time of Object creation while method(s) can be called any numbers of time.
 
